+- `library/factual/tao-circuit-feature-ledger/tao-likeness-requires-a-five-part-canonicalization-screen.md`
+
+## Findings
+
+### 1. The frozen package to screen
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Exploration 001 narrowed the branch to a provisional package:
+  `stretching/enstrophy bottleneck` +
+  `dyadic coupled fluxes` +
+  `role-labeled helical packet Tao screen`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Exploration 002 sharpened that package:
+  the exact ledger lives only at the Fourier/Leray helical-triad core, and the
+  dyadic package is only an aggregation of that exact core.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The same exploration also showed that the only clear
+  Tao-sensitive feature is exact packet rigidity plus unavoidable
+  spectator/conjugate couplings, not generic energy/helicity flux language.
+
+### 2. Prior-art screen
+
+| Prior-art family | Overlap assessment | Distinctness verdict |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| Waleffe-type triad analysis | `[VERIFIED]` very close at the exact-ledger level. The branch's sharpest exact content is helical-triad coefficient rigidity and conservation constraints. | `[INFERRED]` not distinct at theorem-facing gain level; only the packet-complete Tao comparison is narrower. |
+| Helical decimation | `[VERIFIED]` the branch rejects filtered same-sign sectors as success criteria, but the positive-looking transfer stories remain adjacent to that literature. | `[INFERRED]` distinct only because the branch insists on full packet completion and mixed-helicity restoration; otherwise it would collapse immediately. |
+| Shell-model intuition | `[VERIFIED]` the Tao comparison itself is shell/circuit facing, and the attack file warns that shell-style favorable transfer can become decorative. | `[INFERRED]` shell intuition is a comparator, not a new mechanism; it does not produce a theorem-facing NS gain here. |
+| Same-helicity favorable-sector lore | `[VERIFIED]` the branch and its critiques repeatedly treat this as a novelty trap. | `[VERIFIED]` not distinct unless it carries a quantitatively relevant full-burden share after mixed-helicity restoration, which the record does not provide. |
+
+### 3. What is genuinely distinct, and what is not
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The package is **not** genuinely distinct at the level of a
+  theorem-facing gain on a stretching/enstrophy burden.
+- `[INFERRED]` The only serious distinct element is narrower:
+  exact NS packet-complete rigidity with forced conjugate and spectator
+  couplings, used as a Tao discriminator.
+- `[VERIFIED]` That distinct element does not rescue the branch from overlap in
+  the sense relevant to Step 11, because it remains a discriminator without a
+  one-sided gain.
+- `[VERIFIED]` So the branch is:
+  - not merely recycled same-helicity folklore;
+  - but still too prior-art-adjacent and too non-coercive to justify Step 2.
+
+### 4. Typed obstruction analysis
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` `setup obstruction` is already live:
+  Exploration 001 could not freeze the baseline cash-out or the minimum gain
+  threshold in the same burden currency.
+- `[VERIFIED]` `calibration obstruction` is also live:
+  Exploration 002 made the Tao screen operational but did not produce a
+  theorem-facing one-sided gain from the coupled ledger.
+- `[INFERRED]` `prior-art overlap obstruction` is material but secondary:
+  the package stays adjacent to Waleffe/helical-decimation/shell/same-helicity
+  families, yet one narrow packet-level Tao discriminator prevents the branch
+  from collapsing into pure repackaging.
+- `[INFERRED]` The narrowest honest first label is therefore:
+  `setup obstruction, with calibration obstruction and prior-art-adjacent non-coercivity as supporting reasons`.
+
+### 5. Step-2 freeze if any
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` No Step-2 freeze is earned.
+- Reason:
+  Step 2 would require a concretely frozen baseline criterion, minimum gain
+  threshold, and named bad term or bad transfer pattern in theorem-facing
+  burden language.
+  Step 11 still lacks those items.
+
+## Conclusion
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The prior-art screen does not rescue the branch.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The branch has one real NS-sensitive discriminator, but no
+  source-backed one-sided, localization-stable, endpoint-relevant gain.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Because the setup lock is still incomplete and the calibrated
+  Tao-sensitive feature remains exact-but-noncoercive, the branch should stop
+  before the coercivity gate.
+- Explicit Step-11 recommendation:
+  `setup obstruction, branch should stop before coercivity gate`

